cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.PL

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it presents a system for secure multi-party computation protocols. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with converting TensorFlow inference code and real-world neural networks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it involves distributed computation. It may also fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it involves building components and a compiler. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.PL (Programming Languages) as it involves a float-to-fixed compiler.
